Jainism

The first official Jain temple was established in Toronto in 1988. This temple served both the Digambar and Svetambara communities.

Sikhism

Sikhs are the largest religious group among Indo-Canadians. According to the 2001 census there are 278,410 Sikhs in Canada. Sikhs have been in Canada since at least 1887.
