Age and religion

According to the 2001 census, the major religions in Canada have the following median age. Canada has a median age of 37.3.

*Presbyterian 46.1
*United Church 44.1
*Anglican 43.8
*Lutheran 43.3
*Jewish 41.5
*Greek Orthodox 40.7
*Baptist 39.3
*Buddhist 38.0
*Roman Catholic 37.8
*Pentecostal 33.5
*No Religion 31.9
*Hindu 30.2
*Sikh 29.7
*Muslim 28.1

